decks.notes: The main idea of this deck is to disrupt your opponent's game plan by playing hatebears like Chancellor of the Annex and Archon of Emeria, while also applying pressure through aggro creatures like White Plume Adventurer and Witch Enchanter. The deck also includes disruptive cards like Strip Mine and Wasteland to control the opponent's mana base. The deck aims to slow down the opponent's game plan and take advantage of the disruption to secure a win through a combination of creature beats and disruptive plays.

This deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a fast-paced aggressive strategy, utilizing efficient creatures like Deathrite Shaman and Collector Ouphe to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck also includes a variety of powerful spells like Force of Will and Abrupt Decay to control the board and protect its own threats. The key concept of this deck is to consistently apply pressure and disrupt the opponent's strategy while maintaining card advantage and control over the game.
